# ATAK Plugin UI Expert (UV-PRO / Darksteal)

Primary responsibility: **settings and plugin UI** — layout, typography, color, alignment, summaries, disabled states, scroll stability.

## Default: ATAK standard

Follow **MeshcoreAtak** as the baseline unless the user overrides:

- `PluginPreferenceFragment` + `preferences.xml` with Pan widgets (`PanCheckBoxPreference`, `PanListPreference`, `PanEditTextPreference`)
- `PreferenceCategory` for sections — native ATAK rendering (no ListView row hacks)
- Dynamic values via `updateSummaries()` and plain or Spannable `pref.setSummary()` — not manual TextView walks on scroll
- Shared prefs via ATAK `MapView` context, not plugin context

## UV-PRO custom UI (keep unless user changes it)

When working on Darksteal Tool Preferences, **preserve** established styling:

- **Category headers**: yellow (`#FFEB3B`), bold, 18sp, **centered** (Beacon, Radio, APRS, Security, Administrative)
- **Smart Beacon / SA Relay sub-headers**: blue (`#FF1976D2`), bold, **left-aligned**
- **Setting titles**: white, 16sp
- **Summaries**: white description line + **green** (`#4CAF50`) value line, 16sp, two rows
- **Admin-gated rows**: grey when locked/disabled
- Admin toggle + password gate at top of Administrative Settings

## Scroll-safe implementation

- **Do not** call `setLayoutResource(R.layout.*)` on preferences — ATAK inflates rows with host `Resources`, causing `Resources$NotFoundException` and crashes
- Style rows in `applyRowStyles()` on bind: centered yellow categories, white/green summaries, reset left-align on standard rows every bind
- Re-apply summary spannables when Pan widgets overwrite them on bind

## Before calling UI done

- Scroll the full list: no alignment jumping, no grey unreadable text
- Categories stay centered/yellow; normal rows stay left/white
- List prefs (Retry Interval, Max Retries, APRS SSID) show green values
- Disabled admin children are visibly greyed

Do not revert UI to plain Meshcore-style summaries unless the user explicitly asks.
